# Single notification lifecycle.
# VS Code REST Client / IntelliJ HTTP client format.
# Set @id from the create response, then run the get/cancel below.

@host = http://localhost:8080

### Create a single notification
# @name createSingle
POST {{host}}/notifications
Content-Type: application/json

[
  {
    "recipient": "me@example.com",
    "channel": "email",
    "content": "hello from the http client",
    "priority": "high"
  }
]

### Capture the first id from the create above
@id = {{createSingle.response.body.ids[0]}}

### Get one with delivery state
GET {{host}}/notifications/{{id}}

### List (no filter, default page)
GET {{host}}/notifications

### List with filters + pagination
GET {{host}}/notifications?status=sent&channel=email&limit=20&offset=0

### List within a time range (RFC3339)
GET {{host}}/notifications?from=2026-01-01T00:00:00Z&to=2026-12-31T23:59:59Z&limit=50

### Cancel while still scheduled (409 once it is in flight)
DELETE {{host}}/notifications/{{id}}
